This paper is about semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of neural attention and encoder-decoder models suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and computational linguistics. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques such as neural networks and attention mechanisms suggests that this paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on generating logical forms also suggests that this paper could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with neural networks and their applications. Finally, the use of natural language understanding and information retrieval techniques suggests that this paper could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
